      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're correct to be concerned. Looking at the code more carefully:\n\n**Current behavior: Parsing failures are completely silent with no error logging.**\n\nIn `src/tools/parser.rs`, lines 399-417, the `try_parse_tool_call()` function uses:\n\n```rust\nfn try_parse_tool_call(json_str: &str) -> Option<ToolCall> {\n    let value: serde_json::Value = serde_json::from_str(json_str).ok()?;\n    // ... rest of parsing\n}\n```\n\nThe `.ok()?` operator converts the `Result<Value, Error>` into an `Option<Value>`, **discarding the error**. This means:\n\n1. **JSON syntax errors** (malformed JSON inside `<function_call>`) are silently ignored\n2. **Missing required fields** (like `name` or `arguments`) return `None` with no indication why\n3. **No trace logging** exists for these failures\n\nThis is problematic for debugging because if a model generates a malformed tool call, you won't know:\n- That it happened\n- What was malformed\n- What the actual content was\n\n**What you should add:**\n\n```rust\nfn try_parse_tool_call(json_str: &str) -> Option<ToolCall> {\n    let value: serde_json::Value = match serde_json::from_str(json_str) {\n        Ok(v) => v,\n        Err(e) => {\n            tracing::warn!(\n                error = %e,\n                json_content = %json_str,\n                \"Failed to parse JSON from function_call block\"\n            );\n            return None;\n        }\n    };\n    \n    let fc = match value.get(\"function_call\") {\n        Some(f) => f,\n        None => {\n            tracing::warn!(\n                json_content = %json_str,\n                \"Missing 'function_call' key in tool call JSON\"\n            );\n            return None;\n        }\n    };\n\n    let name = match fc.get(\"name\").and_then(|v| v.as_str()) {\n        Some(n) => n.to_string(),\n        None => {\n            tracing::warn!(\n                json_content = %json_str,\n                \"Missing or invalid 'name' field in function_call\"\n            );\n            return None;\n        }\n    };\n\n    // ... rest of the function\n}\n```\n\nSimilar logging should be added to `try_parse_xml_invoke()` for XML parsing failures.\n\nThis would make debugging tool call issues much easier, especially when running with `--log-level debug` or `--log-level trace`."
